    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-01-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-01-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="300"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d300">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.70/57</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="69" xml:id="d300fn69">This document is in reply to the Department’s <hi
                            rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> of December 17, 1938, <ref
                            target="frus1938v04#pg_553">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1938, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p. 553</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Aide-Mémoire</hi>
                </p>
                <p>His Majesty’s Consul-General at Shanghai has been instructed to reply to the
                    Eastern Extension Telegraph Company along the same lines as the answer already
                    given to the American Company by the United States Consul-General. It is
                    understood that the Danish Consul-General has also given the same advice to the
                    Great Northern Telegraph Company.</p>
                <p>There has been no fresh development since December 12th and in the circumstances
                    His Majesty’s Government agree that representations at Tokyo should be deferred
                    for the time being.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-01-07">January 7,
                            1939</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
